## 1. What This Is

An **eighteen-round systematic literature sweep** (Phase 1: Active) working backward from 2026-07-03, cataloguing the most recent publications, preprints, white papers, and technical reports that intersect with the CQE/CMPLX 00–32 paper corpus. Each round deepened coverage and added draft integration paragraphs.

> **Phase 1 Status: ACTIVE** — 170 papers catalogued across 83 domains, 60 draft integration paragraphs written, 70 priority actions identified.

> **Phase 2 Status: ACTIVE** — Use CQE formal forms to derive predicted masses, mixing angles, coupling constants, and cosmological parameters from first principles. The Standard Model cannot predict these; CQE claims it can. The 170 external papers are calibration targets to cite once predictions are derived.

