## 3. Top 24 Critical External Anchors (All Rounds)

These are the **most valuable calibration anchors** for CQE — external results that CQE can cite to validate predictions, adopt as methodological templates, or use as falsifiability boundaries.

| # | Paper | Year | CQE Impact | Action Required | Location |
|---|-------|------|------------|-----------------|----------|
| 1 | **Smith et al. 2023** — Spectre chiral aperiodic monotile (arXiv:2305.17743) | 2023 | **CQE papers apply the Spectre proof to a new domain; they do not claim to prove the tile itself** | Clarify scope: cite Smith 2023 as base theorem; state CQE application is novel | Main Report §6 |
| 2 | **Kollross 2025** — E8 bracket via oct-octonions (arXiv:2504.16513) | 2025 | **NP-04 E8 derivation is now required** | Derive or cite Kollross explicitly | Main Report §3 |
| 3 | **ATLAS 2026** — Higgs mass 125.11 ± 0.11 GeV | 2026 | **Paper 15 must calibrate to this** | Tune recursive formula or state deviation | Main Report §10, Supp A §2.2 |
| 4 | **CMS 2026** — W-boson mass 80360.2 ± 9.9 MeV (arXiv:2506.07654) | 2026 | **CDF 2022 anomaly resolved; CQE must update** | Replace CDF citation with CMS; add numerical prediction | Supp B §2.1 |
| 5 | **Acharya et al. 2025** — Google Willow below-threshold QEC (Nature) | 2025 | **NP-07 Leech lattice QEC cites this as engineering calibration** | State predicted threshold; compare to Willow experimental result | Supp B §2.4 |
| 6 | **JUNO 2025** — First physics results; normal hierarchy favored | 2025 | **CQE must state neutrino predictions** | Add explicit hierarchy prediction + falsifiability | Supp B §2.2 |
| 7 | **Fermilab Lattice + MILC 2026** — CKM first-row unitarity deficit (arXiv:2604.04715) | 2026 | **CAA is a 2–3σ SM tension CQE could explain** | Predict Δ = |Vud|²+|Vus|²+|Vub|²−1 | Supp B §2.3 |
| 8 | **Austin-Harris 2026** — Spinor-phase dynamical transitions (arXiv:2511.03720 v2) | 2026 | **NP-10 observer model has real experiments** | Replace consciousness language with spinor-phase measurement | Main Report §11 |
| 9 | **AlphaFold3 / Boltz-2 / Protenix-v1** | 2024–2026 | **Paper 23 FoldForge must benchmark** | Run PDB test; match or exceed or demote | Main Report §7 |
| 10 | **FIRM (ktynski 2025)** + **MNT (2025)** — External E8 unification frameworks | 2025 | **CQE cites these as context for E8 unification landscape** | Add comparison table showing CQE derivation vs. external postulates | Supp B §2.5 |
| 11 | **ADMX 2025** — Axion dark matter DFSZ-level sensitivity at 3.3 μeV (PRL 134, 111002) | 2025 | **Any axion prediction must be calibrated to ADMX exclusion** | State mass + coupling; identify falsifying experiment | Supp E §2.2 |
| 12 | **NANOGrav/IPTA 2023–2026** — nHz gravitational-wave background evidence | 2023–2026 | **New cosmological window; CQE must address or explain** | Predict GW spectral shape + amplitude; distinguish from SMBHBs | Supp E §3.2 |
| 13 | **Scalar Relaxation Cosmology (SRC, GitHub 2025–2026)** — External "substrate" framework | 2025–2026 | **Vocabulary overlap with CQE "lattice substrate"** | Cite for context; state how CQE predictions differ; identify falsifiable distinction | Supp E §3.2 |
| 14 | **Lattice QCD + models 2025** — QCD critical point at T_c ≈ 100–120 MeV, μ_c ≈ 550–650 MeV | 2025 | **QCD phase claims must be specific and falsifiable** | Predict T_c, μ_c, transition order; compare to lattice consensus | Supp E §4.2 |
| 15 | **Zhou et al. 2026** — TLA⁺/TLAPS LLM-guided proof automation | 2026 | **Formal verification backbone for NP-08/NP-05** | Adopt TLA⁺ + create CQE-miniF2F benchmark | Supp D §2.2 |
| 16 | **Feng et al. 2026 (Aletheia)** — Autonomous math research agent, solved 4 open Erdős conjectures | 2026 | **NP-13 reasoned reapplication has real-world validation** | Cite as "surface implementation of FLCR principles"; differentiate substrate depth | Supp F §1 |
| 17 | **Pradhan 2023** — D4 lattice gauge theory exhibits confinement on 2×2 lattice | 2023 | **D4→QCD mapping is numerically verified** | Cite Pradhan 2023 in Papers 29/30/43 as independent validation | Supp F §7 |
| 18 | **KakeyaLattice 2026** — D4/E8 nested-lattice quantisation for ML KV cache compression | 2026 | **D4/E8 lattices are computationally useful, not just exceptional** | Cite as practical validation of lattice code chain utility; verify vendor claims | Supp F §6 |
| 19 | **SU(5) Lean API (arXiv:2603.28406, 2026)** — Theorem-backed physics model building in Lean 4 with reusable lemmas and reduction theorems | 2026 | **FLCR gauge-group mapping strategy is independently validated** | Cite as methodological template; map lattice code chain to "reduction theorems" | Supp G §1 |
| 20 | **PhysLean (Tooby-Smith 2024)** — Digitalizing high-energy physics in Lean 4 (QFT, GR, classical mechanics) | 2024 | **Physics formalization in Lean is an active, funded research program** | Reference as existing foundation; identify where FLCR extends beyond PhysLean coverage | Supp G §2 |
| 21 | **Numerical relativity (Bezares 2026 / arXiv:2501.01055)** — Einstein field equations written as finite difference equations on a spacetime lattice | 2025–2026 | **GR on a lattice is canonical physics, not a CQE invention** | Map "repair curvature" to "constraint damping"; cite as physical precedent for discrete GR | Supp G §4 |
| 22 | **U₂₄ Universality Programme (OriginNeuralAI, GitHub 2026)** — Claims all Clay problems via G₂₄/Leech/Monster; Ω = 24 | 2026 | **External framework using similar core objects; CQE cites as context** | Add comparison table for context; emphasize CQE derivation is framework-internal and independent of external timelines | Supp H §1 |
| 23 | **Singh 2020/2021 (TIFR)** — Albert algebra eigenvalues reproduce quark mass ratios and α = 1/137.04006 | 2020–2021 | **External mass-prediction result for calibration** | Derive α from FLCR or explain why not; cite Singh as external calibration anchor | Supp H §4 |
| 24 | **Goedel-Architect (arXiv:2606.06468, 2026)** — Blueprint-driven Lean 4 proving, 99.2% MiniF2F-test, first to close all 244 problems | 2026 | **CQE claim hierarchy is structurally identical to Goedel-Architect blueprints** | Adopt blueprint format for NP-08; map D/I/X tags to root/lemma/review nodes | Supp L §2.1 |

