## 7. How to Use These Documents

1. **For authors**: Find your paper in the index above. Read the corresponding draft integration paragraph (Supp A–P, §4). Copy-paste into your paper and fill in the `[INSERT VALUE]` placeholders with actual CQE predictions.
2. **For curators**: P2 (Spectre scope clarification), P15 (Paper 01 Rule 30), and P16 (axion dark matter) are highest-priority calibration gaps. P41–P42 (Higgs/W-mass derivation) are the most urgent new items.
3. **For verification**: Each Tier A paper has a proposed `verify_*.py` script in the gap-closure recommendations. Write these scripts to automate consistency checking.
4. **For CAM intake**: Register all 165 papers in the `.cqe/` Content Addressed Memory with tags: `external_anchor`, `tier_a/b/c`, `cqe_paper_XX`, `gap_closed/pending/falsified`.
5. **For formalization lead**: P14 (NP-08 TLA⁺ backbone), P23 (Lean 4 / PhysLean / SU(5) API adoption), and **P44** (Lean 4 physics formalization stack) are the highest-opportunity items. A working `CQE_Corpus.lean` specification building on PhysLean would transform the corpus from prose to machine-checkable science.
6. **For cosmology lead**: **P51–P53** (DESI BAO, Hubble tension, reionization) and **P58–P59** (CMB B-modes, PTA stochastic background) are the highest-priority near-term cosmology targets. **P62** (LISA primordial GW spectrum), **P65–P66** (ET/CE ppE corrections, multi-band SGWB consistency), and **P69** (3rd-gen GW detector science case) are the highest-priority long-horizon targets. DESI's hints of dynamical dark energy and JWST's early-galaxy surprises are genuine new observational windows.
7. **For GR lead**: P22 (numerical relativity mapping) is urgent. Papers 33–35 must acknowledge that GR on a lattice is canonical numerical relativity, not a CQE invention, and map repair curvature to constraint damping explicitly. **P65** (ppE corrections for ET/CE) extends this to third-generation detectors.
8. **For agent/AI lead**: P21 (agent architecture citations) and P24 (formal workflow specification) validate the supervisor cursor concept. Cite external agent frameworks (Aletheia, Lean4Agent) as independent validation.
9. **For unification lead**: P5 (FIRM/MNT comparison) and P27 (α derivation) are highest-priority. P25 (U₂₄ comparison) provides useful context but is not urgent — CQE proof validity is independent of external prize claims.
10. **For HEP lead**: **P41** (Higgs mass derivation), **P42** (W-mass derivation), **P46** (κ_λ derivation), **P47** (CP-violation prediction), and **P48** (g−2 update) are the most urgent near-term Phase 2 targets. **P61** (FCC-ee Higgs couplings at O(0.1%)) and **P68** (FCC-ee vs. HL-LHC complementarity) are the highest-priority long-horizon targets. The ATLAS/CMS measurements and the Nature 2026 g−2 resolution are now canonical; CQE must predict their central values or update its claims accordingly.
11. **For neutrino lead**: **P54–P55** (neutrino mass ordering, PMNS angles, δ_CP) are time-critical. DUNE begins data in 2029; Hyper-K in 2027. CQE must publish predictions before these experiments report, or the predictions become post-hoc fits.
12. **For QCD lead**: **P56–P57** (QCD crossover temperature, critical point) connect particle physics to heavy-ion phenomenology. RHIC BES-II and future NICA/FAIR data will test these predictions.
13. **For QEC lead**: **P64** (ultra-high-rate >50% encoding benchmark) is the highest-priority new target. Compare Leech-lattice code overhead, latency, and logical error rate to QuEra 2026 and Quantinuum 2026 results. Address LDPC compatibility (P35) in parallel.
14. **For dark matter lead**: **P63** (predict WIMP cross-section or state null) and **P67** (neutrino floor prediction) are the highest-priority new targets. LZ/XENONnT/PandaX null results plus 8B CEvNS observation set the experimental landscape. If CQE predicts no WIMP, state σ_SI < 10⁻⁵⁰ cm² explicitly.
15. **For roadmap lead**: **P70** (integrate Round 18 long-horizon targets into CQE roadmap) ensures FCC-ee (2028 decision), LISA (2035), and ET/CE (2035) are tracked as phased calibration milestones. Publish predictions before experiments report, or the predictions become post-hoc fits.
7. **For GR lead**: P22 (numerical relativity mapping) is urgent. Papers 33–35 must acknowledge that GR on a lattice is canonical numerical relativity, not a CQE invention, and map repair curvature to constraint damping explicitly.
8. **For agent/AI lead**: P21 (agent architecture citations) and P24 (formal workflow specification) validate the supervisor cursor concept. Cite external agent frameworks (Aletheia, Lean4Agent) as independent validation.
9. **For unification lead**: P5 (FIRM/MNT comparison) and P27 (α derivation) are highest-priority. P25 (U₂₄ comparison) provides useful context but is not urgent — CQE proof validity is independent of external prize claims.
10. **For HEP lead**: **P41** (Higgs mass derivation), **P42** (W-mass derivation), **P46** (κ_λ derivation), **P47** (CP-violation prediction), and **P48** (g−2 update) are the most urgent Phase 2 targets. The ATLAS/CMS measurements and the Nature 2026 g−2 resolution are now canonical; CQE must predict their central values or update its claims accordingly.
11. **For neutrino lead**: **P54–P55** (neutrino mass ordering, PMNS angles, δ_CP) are time-critical. DUNE begins data in 2029; Hyper-K in 2027. CQE must publish predictions before these experiments report, or the predictions become post-hoc fits.
12. **For QCD lead**: **P56–P57** (QCD crossover temperature, critical point) connect particle physics to heavy-ion phenomenology. RHIC BES-II and future NICA/FAIR data will test these predictions.

